history.content: it kinda looks like all the waitlisted people is waitlisted because the lab that they close is full, i.e. if you dropped and added into an open lab you would get in. Don't quote me on this though just in case I'm wrong.

Respondent is correct. If you're on the waiting list but signed up for a lab that's full, you should drop the class and re-add, signing up for a lab with room in it or you won't get in. Seems like the system should be able to shuffle you around, but....no.

When will automatic placement into the class off the waitlist start? Is there an order for classes to follow in the adjustment period? There are over a hundred positions left and less than that number of open seats. Should I just sit tight or should i drop the class and try to add it?
